race.comment: KUROSHINZO (6) was too good for a maiden field last start over 1200m at Dubbo. Reunites with Wendy Peel who was on board last start. No reason he cannot win again from the low draw. THINK I'M IRISH (3) was unplaced two runs back then again missed the frame when seventh over 1600m at Hawkesbury. Will roll forward and give a ton of cheek. DERVINIA (5) is some chance in what looks a rather open race. She was a good winner two back at Narromine and while she couldn't repeat the effort last start, that rating still holds some weight. Can't be discounted with no weight on her back. MY CROWN (4) got the job done here two back before jumping straight to the mile last time out. Back to 1400m today looks a good move and a better run is on the cards.
